[Crim. No. 3268. In Bank. July 15, 1929.] In the Matter of LEONARD T. MAYHEW on Habeas Corpus.

*561G. E. Harpham for Petitioner.

No appearance for Respondent.

THE COURT.

Petition for rehearing on appli cation for habeas corpus is denied. (See People v. Plum, 97 Cal. App. 253 [275 Pac. 518] ; People v. Plum, 88 Cal. App. 575 [263 Pac. 862], on rehearing, 88 Cal. App. 585 [265 Pac. 322]; People v. Manchell, 91 Cal. App. 788 [267 Pac. 718].)
